1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Your phone battery works by shuttling lithium ions between two electrodes.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:09,600
When charging, lithium ions move from the positive electrode to the negative one.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,000
Discharging?

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,200
The process flips!

5
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,600
Ions travel back to release energy.

6
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:17,600
This movement creates a flow of electrons, powering your device!

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:22,000
So, next time you charge, remember those tiny ions at work.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Curious about more tech secrets?

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Like and follow for more!
